<p>
The seminar will meet on Mondays, 3:00PM-4:00PM in LGRT 206. 
</p>
<br><hr><br>

<b>Schedule</b>
<br>
<br>
1/23. Organizational meeting, 4:30PM, LGRT 1634. 
<br>
<br>
2/2. Snow day.
<br>
<br>
2/9. Snow day.
<br>
<br>
2/17. Paul Hacking. <em>Stable bundles and integrable systems</em>. 3:00PM, LGRT 206.
<br>
Note that we are meeting on Tuesday (= UMass Monday) due to Presidents' day.
<br>
<br>
2/23. Eyal Markman. <em>Meromorphic Higgs pairs</em>. 3:00PM, LGRT 206.
<br>
<br>
3/2. Alexei Oblomkov. <em>The Hitchin system for the projective line</em>. 3:00PM, LGRT 206.
<br>
<br>
3/9. Tassos Vogiannou. <em>Character varieties</em>. 3:00PM, LGRT 206.
<br>
<br>
3/16. No meeting (Spring break).
<br>
<br>
3/23. Jenia Tevelev. <em>Geodesic flow on an ellipsoid</em>. 3:00PM, LGRT 206.
<br>
<br>
3/30. Kien Nguyen. <em>Geodesic flow on an ellipsoid. II</em>. 3:00PM, LGRT 206.
<br>
<br>
4/6. Franz Pedit. <em>Harmonic maps, spectral curves and completely integrable systems</em>. 3:00PM, LGRT 206.
<br>
